### 9.2 Entity Descriptions

**User Entity:**
The User entity represents system users including customers and administrators. It stores authentication credentials, personal information, and role assignments. The entity implements Spring Security's UserDetails interface for integration with the security framework.

Key attributes:
- id: Primary key, auto-generated
- email: Unique identifier for login, must be unique
- password: Encrypted password using BCrypt
- firstName, lastName: User's name
- phoneNumber: Contact information
- role: Enum (CUSTOMER, ADMIN) for access control
- enabled: Boolean flag for account status
- createdAt, updatedAt: Timestamp tracking

Relationships:
- One-to-one with Cart
- One-to-many with Order

**Product Entity:**
The Product entity stores information about items available for purchase. It includes pricing, inventory, and categorization information.

Key attributes:
- id: Primary key, auto-generated
- name: Product name
- description: Detailed product information
- price: Product price as BigDecimal for precision
- stockQuantity: Available inventory count
- category: Product category for filtering
- brand: Product brand
- imageUrl: Product image reference
- active: Soft delete flag
- createdAt, updatedAt: Timestamp tracking

Relationships:
- One-to-many with CartItem
- One-to-many with OrderItem

**Cart Entity:**
The Cart entity represents a user's shopping cart. Each user has exactly one cart, created automatically upon registration.

Key attributes:
- id: Primary key, auto-generated
- user: One-to-one relationship with User
- items: Collection of CartItems
- createdAt, updatedAt: Timestamp tracking

Relationships:
- One-to-one with User
- One-to-many with CartItem

**CartItem Entity:**
CartItem represents a product added to a cart with a specific quantity.

Key attributes:
- id: Primary key, auto-generated
- cart: Many-to-one relationship with Cart
- product: Many-to-one relationship with Product
- quantity: Number of items
- addedAt: Timestamp when item was added

Relationships:
- Many-to-one with Cart
- Many-to-one with Product

**Order Entity:**
The Order entity represents a completed purchase transaction. It contains order details, status, and shipping information.

Key attributes:
- id: Primary key, auto-generated
- user: Many-to-one relationship with User
- items: Collection of OrderItems
- totalAmount: Calculated total price
- status: Enum (PENDING, CONFIRMED, SHIPPED, DELIVERED, CANCELLED)
- shippingAddress: Delivery address
- paymentMethod: Payment information
- createdAt, updatedAt: Timestamp tracking

Relationships:
- Many-to-one with User
- One-to-many with OrderItem

**OrderItem Entity:**
OrderItem represents a product included in an order with quantity and price at time of purchase.

Key attributes:
- id: Primary key, auto-generated
- order: Many-to-one relationship with Order
- product: Many-to-one relationship with Product
- quantity: Number of items ordered
- price: Price at time of order (snapshot)

Relationships:
- Many-to-one with Order
- Many-to-one with Product

### 9.3 Database Normalization

The database design follows third normal form (3NF):
- Each entity has a primary key
- No redundant data storage
- Proper foreign key relationships
- Atomic values in each field

### 9.4 Indexes and Performance

Indexes are automatically created on:
- Primary keys (id fields)
- Foreign keys (user_id, cart_id, product_id, order_id)
- Unique constraints (email in User table)

Additional indexes could be added for:
- Product category and brand for faster filtering
- Order status for admin queries
- User email for faster authentication lookups

