## 11. Security Implementation

### 11.1 Authentication Flow

The authentication flow follows these steps:

1. **Registration:**
   - Client sends registration request with user details
   - Server validates input data
   - Server checks email uniqueness
   - Server encrypts password using BCrypt
   - Server creates user and cart
   - Server generates JWT token
   - Server returns token to client

2. **Login:**
   - Client sends login request with credentials
   - Server validates credentials using AuthenticationManager
   - Server generates JWT token
   - Server returns token to client

3. **Authenticated Requests:**
   - Client includes JWT token in Authorization header
   - JwtAuthenticationFilter intercepts request
   - Filter extracts token from header
   - Filter validates token signature and expiration
   - Filter loads user details
   - Filter sets authentication in security context
   - Request proceeds to controller

### 11.2 JWT Implementation

**Token Structure:**
JWT tokens consist of three parts separated by dots:
- Header: Algorithm and token type
- Payload: Claims (email, issued at, expiration)
- Signature: HMAC SHA256 signature

**Token Generation:**
- Uses jjwt library
- Sets subject as user email
- Sets issued at time
- Sets expiration (24 hours)
- Signs with secret key

**Token Validation:**
- Extracts token from Authorization header
- Parses token to extract claims
- Validates signature
- Checks expiration
- Verifies user exists

### 11.3 Password Security

**BCrypt Hashing:**
- Uses BCryptPasswordEncoder
- Automatic salt generation
- Adaptive hashing (10 rounds)
- One-way encryption

**Password Validation:**
- Minimum 6 characters required
- Validated using Jakarta Validation
- No password complexity requirements (can be enhanced)

### 11.4 Role-Based Access Control

**Role Implementation:**
- Roles stored as enum in User entity
- CUSTOMER: Standard user access
- ADMIN: Full system access

**Access Control:**
- Method-level security using @PreAuthorize
- Role checks in SecurityConfig
- Endpoint protection based on roles

**Protected Endpoints:**
- Admin endpoints require ADMIN role
- Cart and order endpoints require authentication
- Product viewing is public
- Product modification requires ADMIN role

### 11.5 Security Configuration

**Security Filter Chain:**
- Public endpoints: /api/auth/**, /api/products/**, /h2-console/**
- Protected endpoints: All others require authentication
- Admin endpoints: /api/admin/** requires ADMIN role

**CORS Configuration:**
- Allows all origins (can be restricted in production)
- Supports all HTTP methods
- Allows all headers

**Session Management:**
- Stateless session management
- No server-side session storage
- JWT tokens handle authentication state

